---
source: tests/cli_golden.rs
expression: help
---
AURA CLI - Autonomous Universal Reasoning Architecture

Usage: aura [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  run      Run the agent (default when no subcommand is given)
  login    Authenticate with zOS to obtain a JWT for proxy mode
  logout   Clear stored authentication credentials
  whoami   Show current authentication status
  hello    Print "Hello, World!" and exit (Spec 01)
  migrate  Phase 4a stub: migrate aura state (no-op today)
  plugins  Manage declarative plugins (Phase 4b)
  agents   Inspect / manage live + orphaned subagents (Phase 7b)
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --mode <MODE>
          Phase 9: top-level `AgentMode` override. Highest rung of the documented resolution priority chain (CLI > TUI slash > SDK field > daemon default > `AgentMode::Agent` fallback). The flag is resolved at session start by the fleet daemon's `resolve_session_mode` helper

          Possible values:
          - agent: Full unrestricted operation subject to user permissions
          - plan:  Read + markdown writes + read-only subprocesses
          - ask:   Read-only
          - debug: Read + sandboxed probes only

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
